According to Quinn's mother, Rachel Nystrom, the only other person in their extended family known to have diabetes is Quinn's great uncle on her father's side, who was diagnosed with type 1 diabetes at age 25 and who is now in his mid-tolate 60s.
"Other than that, there is no one else," Mrs. Nystrom says.
The Nystrom's oldest child, Quinn's brother Thor, has not developed diabetes.
But, as the family is well aware, with diabetes, there are no guarantees.
