Chocolate is my favorite food, and I was being told to be careful about my diet."
To add to her woes, that summer Quinn's parents enrolled her in a camp for young people with diabetes.
"Can you imagine a teenager with diabetes going to a place called Camp Needlepoint?" exclaims Quinn.
By her own admission, Quinn went to the camp that year kicking and screaming.
"It was a physical struggle just to get me there," she says.
