Because of the large number of genes possibly involved and the differences in their relative contribution to the disease process, identifying those genes associated with diabetes is a major challenge for researchers.
However, the National Institutes of Health (NIH) is employing a multifaceted approach to understanding the genetic factors contributing to diabetes.
These efforts include research consortia, large-scale genome-wide scans, microarray technology, and animal studies.
